<p id="2sYxfb"><em>Elantris</em> doesn’t currently have a sequel, but the Hugo Award-winning novella <a href="https://www.amazon.com/Emperors-Soul-10th-Anniversary-Special/dp/1616964022/?tag=polygon05-20" rel="sponsored nofollow noopener" target="_blank" has-subtag="true" data-cdata='{"rewritten_url":"https://www.amazon.com/Emperors-Soul-10th-Anniversary-Special/dp/1616964022/?ascsubtag=___pl__p_23873180__m_m-placeholder__s_s-placeholder__t_w__c_c-placeholder__r_r-placeholder__d_d-placeholder\u0026tag=polygon05-20","subtag_max_length":99,"subtag_delim_length":3,"subtag_key":"ascsubtag","subtag_data":{"ascsubtag":"___pl__p_23873180__m_m-placeholder__s_s-placeholder__t_w__c_c-placeholder__r_r-placeholder__d_d-placeholder","tag":"polygon05-20"},"encode_subtag":false}'><em>The Emperor’s Soul</em></a><em> </em>shares its setting. (Technically, so do a lot of Sanderson’s books, but I’ll get to that later.) <em>The Emperor’s Soul</em>, which tells the tale of a jailed forger given an impossible task, is also on Sanderson’s list of good starting points. It’s perfect if you want to get a tiny taste of the level of creativity and detail the author brings to the genre without much commitment.</p>
<p id="lwWqgf">My personal favorite Sanderson book is <a href="https://www.amazon.com/Warbreaker-Brandon-Sanderson/dp/0765360039/?tag=polygon05-20" rel="sponsored nofollow noopener" target="_blank" has-subtag="true" data-cdata='{"rewritten_url":"https://www.amazon.com/Warbreaker-Brandon-Sanderson/dp/0765360039/?ascsubtag=___pl__p_23873180__m_m-placeholder__s_s-placeholder__t_w__c_c-placeholder__r_r-placeholder__d_d-placeholder\u0026tag=polygon05-20","subtag_max_length":99,"subtag_delim_length":3,"subtag_key":"ascsubtag","subtag_data":{"ascsubtag":"___pl__p_23873180__m_m-placeholder__s_s-placeholder__t_w__c_c-placeholder__r_r-placeholder__d_d-placeholder","tag":"polygon05-20"},"encode_subtag":false}'><em>Warbreaker</em></a>, and it’s where Sanderson recommends fans who like a good romance begin. <em>Warbreaker</em> follows a princess wedded to a terrifying God King, her sister on a mission to save her, and an amnesiac trying to puzzle out the mystery of his own past and the truth about his faith. The book stands alone, but it’s a must-read if you want to delve into Sanderson’s later books given that some of its characters appear in his Stormlight Archive series.</p>
<div id="MhEJcA">
<div class="c-product-card__component c-product-card c-product-card--three-buttons">
