<p id="xT2wtb"><em>The Way of Kings </em>starts off much like many of Sanderson’s other books, introducing a fascinating world and a big cast of characters. The world of Roshar is filled with squabbling princes, giant crabs with gems for hearts, powerful storms, and warriors carrying oversized swords. Along with releasing four 1,000-plus-page books in the series so far, Sanderson has also published two Stormlight Archive novellas, <a href="https://www.amazon.com/Edgedancer-Stormlight-Archive-Brandon-Sanderson/dp/1250166543?tag=polygon05-20" rel="sponsored nofollow noopener" target="_blank" has-subtag="true" data-cdata='{"rewritten_url":"https://www.amazon.com/Edgedancer-Stormlight-Archive-Brandon-Sanderson/dp/1250166543?ascsubtag=___pl__p_23873180__m_m-placeholder__s_s-placeholder__t_w__c_c-placeholder__r_r-placeholder__d_d-placeholder\u0026tag=polygon05-20","subtag_max_length":99,"subtag_delim_length":3,"subtag_key":"ascsubtag","subtag_data":{"ascsubtag":"___pl__p_23873180__m_m-placeholder__s_s-placeholder__t_w__c_c-placeholder__r_r-placeholder__d_d-placeholder","tag":"polygon05-20"},"encode_subtag":false}'><em>Edgedancer</em></a> and <a href="https://www.amazon.com/Dawnshard-Stormlight-Archive-Brandon-Sanderson/dp/1803361069?tag=polygon05-20" rel="sponsored nofollow noopener" target="_blank" has-subtag="true" data-cdata='{"rewritten_url":"https://www.amazon.com/Dawnshard-Stormlight-Archive-Brandon-Sanderson/dp/1803361069?ascsubtag=___pl__p_23873180__m_m-placeholder__s_s-placeholder__t_w__c_c-placeholder__r_r-placeholder__d_d-placeholder\u0026tag=polygon05-20","subtag_max_length":99,"subtag_delim_length":3,"subtag_key":"ascsubtag","subtag_data":{"ascsubtag":"___pl__p_23873180__m_m-placeholder__s_s-placeholder__t_w__c_c-placeholder__r_r-placeholder__d_d-placeholder","tag":"polygon05-20"},"encode_subtag":false}'><em>Dawnshard</em></a>, between books. <em>Edgedancer </em>is a particularly fun read, following a very hungry thief who gets embroiled in a complicated attempt at a succession. The fifth Stormlight Archive<em> </em>book, <a href="https://www.amazon.com/Wind-Truth-Book-Stormlight-Archive/dp/1250319188/?tag=polygon05-20" rel="sponsored nofollow noopener" target="_blank" has-subtag="true" data-cdata='{"rewritten_url":"https://www.amazon.com/Wind-Truth-Book-Stormlight-Archive/dp/1250319188/?ascsubtag=___pl__p_23873180__m_m-placeholder__s_s-placeholder__t_w__c_c-placeholder__r_r-placeholder__d_d-placeholder\u0026tag=polygon05-20","subtag_max_length":99,"subtag_delim_length":3,"subtag_key":"ascsubtag","subtag_data":{"ascsubtag":"___pl__p_23873180__m_m-placeholder__s_s-placeholder__t_w__c_c-placeholder__r_r-placeholder__d_d-placeholder","tag":"polygon05-20"},"encode_subtag":false}'><em>Wind and Truth</em></a>, is due out at the end of this year. </p>
<p id="ES87m4">You can enjoy <em>The Way of Kings </em>without having read any of Sanderson’s other books, but if you have, the series quickly becomes much more complex, with Sanderson’s world-building growing to encompass thousands of years of history spread across multiple planets. The clashes on Roshar turn out to be just a front in a war between Shards that has roped in characters from previous books. Even if you’ve read everything Sanderson’s written, it can be hard to figure out who’s who, since characters often go by different names or hide the full extent of their abilities and knowledge.</p>
<p id="uLPZJe">Working on one epic series would be enough for most authors, but from 2010 to 2022 Sanderson also penned four more Mistborn books, starting with <a href="https://www.amazon.com/Shadows-Self-Mistborn-Brandon-Sanderson-ebook/dp/B00R697CGS?tag=polygon05-20" rel="sponsored nofollow noopener" target="_blank" has-subtag="true" data-cdata='{"rewritten_url":"https://www.amazon.com/Shadows-Self-Mistborn-Brandon-Sanderson-ebook/dp/B00R697CGS?ascsubtag=___pl__p_23873180__m_m-placeholder__s_s-placeholder__t_w__c_c-placeholder__r_r-placeholder__d_d-placeholder\u0026tag=polygon05-20","subtag_max_length":99,"subtag_delim_length":3,"subtag_key":"ascsubtag","subtag_data":{"ascsubtag":"___pl__p_23873180__m_m-placeholder__s_s-placeholder__t_w__c_c-placeholder__r_r-placeholder__d_d-placeholder","tag":"polygon05-20"},"encode_subtag":false}'><em>Shadows of Self</em></a><em> </em>in 2015. These are set 300 years after the original trilogy in a version of the world that’s more akin to urban fantasy or a Western. The characters from the first three books are revered as religious figures, though some are actually still around due to their powers. The events of the fourth book in the series, <a href="https://www.amazon.com/Lost-Metal-Mistborn-Novel/dp/B09N452812/?tag=polygon05-20" rel="sponsored nofollow noopener" target="_blank" has-subtag="true" data-cdata='{"rewritten_url":"https://www.amazon.com/Lost-Metal-Mistborn-Novel/dp/B09N452812/?ascsubtag=___pl__p_23873180__m_m-placeholder__s_s-placeholder__t_w__c_c-placeholder__r_r-placeholder__d_d-placeholder\u0026tag=polygon05-20","subtag_max_length":99,"subtag_delim_length":3,"subtag_key":"ascsubtag","subtag_data":{"ascsubtag":"___pl__p_23873180__m_m-placeholder__s_s-placeholder__t_w__c_c-placeholder__r_r-placeholder__d_d-placeholder","tag":"polygon05-20"},"encode_subtag":false}'><em>The Lost Metal</em></a>, are closely tied to The Stormlight Archive.</p>
<p id="j8TKQs">Reading all of the Cosmere books in order isn’t necessary. You just might be baffled by why there’s a talking sword or who’s explaining the nature of Shards in a chapter’s intro text. The real problem can come if you get hooked and want to go backward in Sanderson’s bibliography, because you may become unknowingly spoiled for some events.</p>
<p id="acQfra">An easy workaround is to read the Cosmere books in the chronological order here:</p>
<ol>
<li id="ZrCABw">
<small><em>Elantris</em></small><small> (2005)</small>
</li>
<li id="mUSpYq">
<small><em>Mistborn</em></small><small> (2006)</small>
</li>
<li id="wFyiMy">
<small><em>The Well of Ascension</em></small><small> (2007)</small>
</li>
<li id="Iv2UID">
<small><em>The Hero of Ages</em></small><small> (2008)</small>
</li>
<li id="AwsynJ">
<small><em>Warbreaker</em></small><small> (2009)</small>
</li>
<li id="pj9jmW">
<small><em>The Way of Kings</em></small><small> (2010)</small>
</li>
<li id="Y25qip">
<small><em>The Alloy of Law</em></small><small> (2011)</small>
</li>
<li id="AIKaub">
<small><em>The Emperor’s Soul</em></small><small> (2012)</small>
</li>
<li id="6Bb1F8">
<small><em>Words of Radiance</em></small><small> (2014)</small>
</li>
<li id="JZu7L1">
<small><em>Shadows of Self</em></small><small> (2015)</small>
</li>
<li id="ZMWrgJ">
<small><em>The Bands of Mourning</em></small><small> (2016)</small>
</li>
<li id="fzVxwV">
<small><em>Edgedancer</em></small><small> (2017)</small>
</li>
<li id="yGkOKG">
<small><em>Oathbringer</em></small><small> (2017)</small>
</li>
<li id="zodGZ7">
<small><em>Dawnshard</em></small><small> (2020)</small>
</li>
<li id="XVcWqq">
<small><em>Rhythm of War</em></small><small> (2020)</small>
</li>
<li id="A3awwe">
<small><em>The Lost Metal</em></small><small> (2022)</small>
</li>
</ol>
<p id="ZlIZVc"></p>
