<p id="15B0Qt">All of the books have since been delivered and are widely for sale. <a href="https://www.amazon.com/Wizards-Handbook-Surviving-Medieval-Projects/dp/1250899680/?tag=polygon05-20" rel="sponsored nofollow noopener" target="_blank" has-subtag="true" data-cdata='{"rewritten_url":"https://www.amazon.com/Wizards-Handbook-Surviving-Medieval-Projects/dp/1250899680/?ascsubtag=___pl__p_23873180__m_m-placeholder__s_s-placeholder__t_w__c_c-placeholder__r_r-placeholder__d_d-placeholder\u0026tag=polygon05-20","subtag_max_length":99,"subtag_delim_length":3,"subtag_key":"ascsubtag","subtag_data":{"ascsubtag":"___pl__p_23873180__m_m-placeholder__s_s-placeholder__t_w__c_c-placeholder__r_r-placeholder__d_d-placeholder","tag":"polygon05-20"},"encode_subtag":false}'><em>The Frugal Wizard’s Handbook for Surviving Medieval England</em></a> is a stand-alone story about an amnesiac time traveler. <a href="https://www.amazon.com/Tress-Emerald-Sea-Cosmere-Projects/dp/1250899664/?tag=polygon05-20" rel="sponsored nofollow noopener" target="_blank" has-subtag="true" data-cdata='{"rewritten_url":"https://www.amazon.com/Tress-Emerald-Sea-Cosmere-Projects/dp/1250899664/?ascsubtag=___pl__p_23873180__m_m-placeholder__s_s-placeholder__t_w__c_c-placeholder__r_r-placeholder__d_d-placeholder\u0026tag=polygon05-20","subtag_max_length":99,"subtag_delim_length":3,"subtag_key":"ascsubtag","subtag_data":{"ascsubtag":"___pl__p_23873180__m_m-placeholder__s_s-placeholder__t_w__c_c-placeholder__r_r-placeholder__d_d-placeholder","tag":"polygon05-20"},"encode_subtag":false}'><em>Tress of the Emerald Sea</em></a><em>, </em><a href="https://www.amazon.com/Yumi-Nightmare-Painter-Cosmere-Projects/dp/1250899702?tag=polygon05-20" rel="sponsored nofollow noopener" target="_blank" has-subtag="true" data-cdata='{"rewritten_url":"https://www.amazon.com/Yumi-Nightmare-Painter-Cosmere-Projects/dp/1250899702?ascsubtag=___pl__p_23873180__m_m-placeholder__s_s-placeholder__t_w__c_c-placeholder__r_r-placeholder__d_d-placeholder\u0026tag=polygon05-20","subtag_max_length":99,"subtag_delim_length":3,"subtag_key":"ascsubtag","subtag_data":{"ascsubtag":"___pl__p_23873180__m_m-placeholder__s_s-placeholder__t_w__c_c-placeholder__r_r-placeholder__d_d-placeholder","tag":"polygon05-20"},"encode_subtag":false}'><em>Yumi and the Nightmare Painter</em></a>,<em> </em>and <a href="https://www.amazon.com/Sunlit-Man-Brandon-Sanderson/dp/1250899710/?tag=polygon05-20" rel="sponsored nofollow noopener" target="_blank" has-subtag="true" data-cdata='{"rewritten_url":"https://www.amazon.com/Sunlit-Man-Brandon-Sanderson/dp/1250899710/?ascsubtag=___pl__p_23873180__m_m-placeholder__s_s-placeholder__t_w__c_c-placeholder__r_r-placeholder__d_d-placeholder\u0026tag=polygon05-20","subtag_max_length":99,"subtag_delim_length":3,"subtag_key":"ascsubtag","subtag_data":{"ascsubtag":"___pl__p_23873180__m_m-placeholder__s_s-placeholder__t_w__c_c-placeholder__r_r-placeholder__d_d-placeholder","tag":"polygon05-20"},"encode_subtag":false}'><em>The Sunlit Man</em></a> are Cosmere novels, each set on a different planet that hasn’t appeared in any of Sanderson’s other works and narrated by Hoid, a mysterious character who is prominent in The Stormlight Archive. </p>
<p id="MAWVbL">They all work as stand-alones, though they do have concepts that are integrated into other series, and knowing Sanderson, they’ll probably tie back into his greater plans eventually. You can read them in any order while waiting for the next Stormlight Archive book or potentially even as an intro to Sanderson based on if you like post-apocalyptic settings (<em>The Sunlit Man</em>), <em>The Princess Bride </em>(<em>Tress of the Emerald Sea</em>), body swapping <em>(Yumi and the Nightmare Painter</em>), or just want to try something that has nothing at all to do with the rest of his bibliography (<em>The Frugal Wizard’s Handbook for Surviving Medieval England</em>).</p>
<p id="YV3cbS">A new secret project is also expected to ship in 2025 as part of a crowdfunding campaign for leather-bound copies of <em>Words of Radiance</em>, the second (and, in my opinion, best so far) book in The Stormlight Archive.</p>
<h2 id="1qX2nw"><strong>Sanderson for young adults</strong></h2>
<p id="xoWobp">While Sanderson’s books often deal with heavy themes like genocide, mental illness, and abuse, he’s never gratuitous or explicit with his sex or violence. He also doesn’t curse, preferring to use swears made up for each world, like “Storms” or “Rust and Ruin.” That means there isn’t anything parents are likely to find objectionable in most of his novels. He’s also written plenty specifically for kids and young adults. The main difference is really the age of the protagonists and the complexity of the plots.</p>
<p id="FDIGIy">The Alcatraz<em> </em>series about a disaster-prone teen was Sanderson’s first entry in kids’ fantasy and now includes six novels. The <a href="https://www.amazon.com/Skyward-Brandon-Sanderson/dp/0399555803/?tag=polygon05-20" rel="sponsored nofollow noopener" target="_blank" has-subtag="true" data-cdata='{"rewritten_url":"https://www.amazon.com/Skyward-Brandon-Sanderson/dp/0399555803/?ascsubtag=___pl__p_23873180__m_m-placeholder__s_s-placeholder__t_w__c_c-placeholder__r_r-placeholder__d_d-placeholder\u0026tag=polygon05-20","subtag_max_length":99,"subtag_delim_length":3,"subtag_key":"ascsubtag","subtag_data":{"ascsubtag":"___pl__p_23873180__m_m-placeholder__s_s-placeholder__t_w__c_c-placeholder__r_r-placeholder__d_d-placeholder","tag":"polygon05-20"},"encode_subtag":false}'>Cytoverse</a> series, which focuses on pilots fighting aliens, includes four novels and three novellas. <a href="https://www.jancipatterson.com/">Janci Patterson</a> worked with Sanderson on some of the entries in both series.</p>
<p id="0SgFj0"><a href="https://www.amazon.com/Steelheart-Reckoners-Brandon-Sanderson/dp/0385743572/?tag=polygon05-20" rel="sponsored nofollow noopener" target="_blank" has-subtag="true" data-cdata='{"rewritten_url":"https://www.amazon.com/Steelheart-Reckoners-Brandon-Sanderson/dp/0385743572/?ascsubtag=___pl__p_23873180__m_m-placeholder__s_s-placeholder__t_w__c_c-placeholder__r_r-placeholder__d_d-placeholder\u0026tag=polygon05-20","subtag_max_length":99,"subtag_delim_length":3,"subtag_key":"ascsubtag","subtag_data":{"ascsubtag":"___pl__p_23873180__m_m-placeholder__s_s-placeholder__t_w__c_c-placeholder__r_r-placeholder__d_d-placeholder","tag":"polygon05-20"},"encode_subtag":false}'>The Reckoners</a> trilogy is Sanderson’s YA exploration of the superhero genre, set in a world where almost everyone with powers is an evil tyrant. <a href="https://www.amazon.com/Rithmatist-Brandon-Sanderson/dp/0765338440?tag=polygon05-20" rel="sponsored nofollow noopener" target="_blank" has-subtag="true" data-cdata='{"rewritten_url":"https://www.amazon.com/Rithmatist-Brandon-Sanderson/dp/0765338440?ascsubtag=___pl__p_23873180__m_m-placeholder__s_s-placeholder__t_w__c_c-placeholder__r_r-placeholder__d_d-placeholder\u0026tag=polygon05-20","subtag_max_length":99,"subtag_delim_length":3,"subtag_key":"ascsubtag","subtag_data":{"ascsubtag":"___pl__p_23873180__m_m-placeholder__s_s-placeholder__t_w__c_c-placeholder__r_r-placeholder__d_d-placeholder","tag":"polygon05-20"},"encode_subtag":false}'><em>The Rithmatist</em></a><em> </em>is a stand-alone magical school novel.</p>
